  "wikitext": "\n'''2-1-005\nAlternative terms: Visible Radiation (G.B.), Visible Radiant Energy (U.S.A.)\n\nAny radiation capable of causing a visual sensation directly.\n\n\nNote: The limits of the spectral range of visible radiation are not well-defined and may vary according to the user.\nThe lower limit is generally taken between 380 and 400 nm and the upper limit between 760 and 780 nm.\n\n1 nanometre (nm) = 10-9m = 1 millimicron.\n\nReference: C.I.E. (modified)\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Light (2)}}\n[[Category:2.1 Optics and Vision]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
